article.headline: Gauchos stage big rally, but falter down the stretch
article.linkText: Detroit's hot shooting too much for UC-Santa Barbara
article.story: SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) -- Willie Green scored 18 of his 24 points in the second half as Detroit defeated California-Santa Barbara 75-59 Saturday. The Titans (14-11) shot 60 percent from the field and held the Gauchos (13-12) to just 34.1 percent. Detroit also outrebounded Santa Barbara, 32-22. The Titans held their biggest lead at 51-33 with 14:29 to go. UC-Santa Barbara rallied to a point, 58-57, by making five 3-pointers in a five-minute span. Branduinn Fullove, the Gauchos' leading scorer with 15 points, hit two of them. But the Gauchos did not make a basket in the final 9:22 and were outscored 17-2 in the final seven minutes. Rulon Harris scored all 13 of his points in the first half to help Detroit take a 36-28 lead at halftime.
